SectionEndorsements.title: As Featured On:
SectionWhyUsMobile.title: We Exist to Empower Workers
SectionWhyUsMobile.step1: On other platforms, managers post jobs and decide on the wages. They rarely pay enough.
SectionWhyUsMobile.step2: We believe employees know their value. We built our marketplace to allow employees to set their own rates.
SectionWhyUsMobile.step3: Other platforms collect up to 40% of the booking amount. This is unfair to their workers.
SectionWhyUsMobile.step4: We charge managers 12%. Our Founding Members pay ZERO.
SectionHowItWorks.createListingLink: PS. You can also become a Café Temps worker!
SectionHowItWorks.part1Text: Use our profile builder to showcase your restaurant experience.
SectionHowItWorks.part1TextC: and accept only the gigs you want.
SectionHowItWorks.part2Text: Managers find workers with the right skills to help them stay open.{pageBreak}We designed search filters to help managers quickly find the perfect talent.
SectionHowItWorks.part3Text: Restaurants fill shifts with Café Temps gig workers.{pageBreak}Workers earn the rate they choose, and restaurants stay open.
SectionHowItWorks.part3Title: Shift is Filled. Worker is Paid.
SectionDifferences.part1Text: In competing gig platforms, managers post jobs and set the price.{pageBreak}We think workers know their own value, so we opted for a direct booking process.
SectionDifferences.part1TextB: In our marketplace, managers must accept the worker's rate to send a booking request.
SectionDifferences.part1TextC: and accept only the gigs you want.
SectionDifferences.part2Text: Happy with your gig worker? You can make an offer to hire them full time.{pageBreak}Unlike our competitors, we don't charge a fee for long-term hires.{pageBreak}We exist to uplift workers, and we are excited when they get new opportunities.
SectionDifferences.part3Text: Competing gig platforms charge 40% fee. We think this cheats their employees.{pageBreak}In comparison, we charge hiring managers a low 12% booking fee.{pageBreak}Workers with Founding Member status pay zero fees, and all other workers pay a 5% platform fee.
SectionHowItWorksNew.WorkerText1: Create a profile and share restaurant experience and key skills. We will verify your identity through a few simple steps.
SectionHowItWorksNew.WorkerText2: You have three hours to accept a booking request before it expires. Accept only the booking requests you want.
SectionHowItWorksNew.WorkerText3: Show up ready to help! The booking request may include details on dress code and other things to know.
SectionHowItWorksNew.WorkerText4: Workers get paid directly into their checking accounts within 48 hours.
SectionHowItWorksNew.WorkerText5: How was the experience at the restaurant? Were the people friendly? Would you do it again?
SectionHowItWorksNew.ManagerText1: Our search filters allow you to locate workers with certain skills, or experience at specific restaurants.
SectionHowItWorksNew.ManagerText2: Great! You found a worker with the right experience. Your worker has three hours to acccept or reject your request.
SectionHowItWorksNew.ManagerText3: Your gig worker arrives! Show him/her around, and give them critical tasks that will allow you to keep serving customers.
SectionHowItWorksNew.ManagerText4: We pay your worker directly. Let us manage the transaction.
SectionHowItWorksNew.ManagerText5: How did the worker do? Did their profile accurately represent their experience and skills? Would you hire them again?
SectionWhyusMobile.Title: Why Join Café Temps?
SectionHowItWorksMobile.WorkerText2: Accept only the requests you want.
SectionHowItWorksMobile.WorkerText4: Get paid directly into your bank account within 48 hours.
SectionHowItWorksMobile.WorkerText5: How was the experience at the restaurant? Would you work there again?
SectionHowItWorksMobile.ManagerText1: Search for specific restaurants and skills.
SectionHowItWorksMobile.ManagerText2: Workers have three hours to respond.
SectionHowItWorksMobile.ManagerText4: We handle all payments. You do nothing.

SectionFees.title: Café Temps Fees
SectionMarkets.title: Our Launch Markets
SectionMarkets.part1Text: We spent months building a talent marketplace for restaurants. We went live in the Summer of 2021.
SectionMarkets.part1Text3: We are recruiting workers in our launch markets
SectionMarkets.part1Text4: Workers that join before the launch date enjoy ZERO fees for life!
SectionMarkets.part1Text5: After each launch date, we invite local restaurants to join
SectionMarkets.part2Text: NYC is Launched! We are now marketing to restaurant owners, caterers, and event planners.
SectionMarkets.part2Text2: We are still recruiting workers here, but new workers in NYC will not receive Founding Member status.
SectionMarkets.part3Text2: We have started our marketing to hiring managers in these cities, but we extended the deadline for Founding Member status to Nov 30. Don't wait!
SectionMarkets.part3Text: All workers that join these cities before  Nov 30 will enjoy Founding Member status with the following benefits:
SectionMarkets.part4Text: We have started recruiting workers in each of these markets.{pageBreak}Join before October 15 and enjoy Founding Member status with no fees FOR LIFE!
SectionFees.WorkerText2: Workers incur a 5% platform fee on their booking income. As example, if a worker generates $100 in bookings, their payout would be $95.
SectionFees.WorkerText: We offer a lifetime fee waiver for workers that join before our Launch Date in each new market.
SectionFees.ManagerText: Restaurants incur a 12% fee on the booking amount. As example, they would incur a $12 fee for each $100 in bookings.
SectionFAQ.title: Frequently Asked Questions
SectionFAQWorker.Answer1: Workers get paid directly into their checking accounts within 48 hours of each booking.
SectionFAQWorker.Answer2: We suggest setting your hourly rate about 50% higher than your normal hourly wage.{pageBreak}Once you get some positive reviews, you may charge even more!
SectionFAQWorker.Answer3: Restaurant managers search worker profiles and send booking requests to the workers in our marketplace.{pageBreak}Make sure your profile is up to date, with a clear profile photo. Your profile description should be fun and engaging. This is your opportunity to advertise yourself!
SectionFAQWorker.Answer4: All workers are treated as independent contractors. Our payment processor (Stripe) will send appropriate tax statements at the end of each calendar year.
SectionFAQWorker.Question5: Do I need a bank account to join as a worker?
SectionFAQWorker.Answer5: Yes, all workers need a valid bank account, since we only send payouts to checking accounts. This reduces the potential for fraud, and helps us verify your identify.
SectionFAQWorker.Question6: Do you share my address publicly?
SectionFAQWorker.Answer6: We do not share your address at anytime.Even hiring managers cannot see your address. {pageBreak}Further, your location on map searches is randomly moved within a radius to make it impossible for someone to locate your address from a simple search.
SectionFAQWorker.Question7: How do I communicate with a manager?
SectionFAQWorker.Answer7: You can send messages to the restaurant manager through your Inbox on Café Temps.
SectionFAQManager.Answer1: Our payment processor uses photo ID and supporting data to validate the identify of every worker. {pageBreak}We also require a valid checking account for each worker.
SectionFAQManager.Question2: How much can I expect to pay?
SectionFAQManager.Answer2: Generally, you should expect to pay 50% to 100% above what you would pay for similar full-time roles. {pageBreak}Remember, Café Temps workers are available on short notice, and you are not paying for any benefits (like health coverage, vacation days, etc.)
SectionFAQManager.Answer3: If a worker does not show up at the booking time, we provide a 100% refund and will remove the worker from our platform.{pageBreak}Beyond this, we do not offer refunds. We encourage restaurants to review each worker to help our talented workers get more gigs.
SectionFAQManager.Answer4: Café Temps does not provide insurance of any kind. We rely on the restaurants to provide their own business coverage in the event of an accident at the location.
SectionFAQManager.Question5: Can I  post a need and let workers apply?
SectionFAQManager.Answer5A: Not yet. We decided on a direct hire process for now, for the following reasons: {pageBreak}(1) We want workers to set their own rates, and not be constrained to the rates of posted jobs.{pageBreak}(2) Job postings work best when there is a large pool of workers in the service area. We are still developing the talent pool at this time. We will consider implementing a gig posting process in the future.
SectionFAQManager.Answer5B: Your booking requests expire after three hours, after which time you may elect to send a booking request to alternate workers.
SectionFAQManager.Question6: What if my worker doesn't meet expectations?
SectionFAQManager.Answer6A: While we hope this rarely happens, sometimes people don't meet our expectations. In these cases, we rely on constructive reviews from restaurant managers to help the worker succeed in future roles.
SectionFAQManager.Answer6B: Keep in mind that each restaurant is unique, and the first day at a new location is challenging for anyone. Be understanding, and give constructive guidance with your worker during their shift.
SectionFAQManager.Question7: How do I communicate with a worker?
SectionFAQManager.Answer7: You can send messages to the worker directly from the worker's profile on Café Temps. Also, after booking you will receive a valid phone number for the worker.
SectionFAQLanding.title: Frequently Asked Questions
SectionFAQLanding.Answer0: Restaurant managers search worker profiles and send booking requests to the workers in our marketplace.{pageBreak}The worker has three hours to accept booking request before they expire.{pageBreak}Make sure your profile is up to date, with a clear profile photo. Your profile description should be fun and engaging. This is your opportunity to advertise yourself!
SectionFAQLanding.Question1: What kind of workers can I find on Café Temps?
SectionFAQLanding.Answer1: We invite all workers to join. This includes caterers, concession staff, and those with experience at both franchise and independent restaurants.{pageBreak}Our search filters allow you to filter on role, experience level, type of restaurant, and even languages spoken. You can even do a keyword search to find workers employed at a certain restaurant.
SectionFAQLanding.Question2: Do I Need Restaurant Experience to Join?
SectionFAQLanding.Answer2: No. While experience is great to have, anyone can join as a restaurant worker. Restaurants and fair concessions often have roles that do not require prior food service experience.
SectionFAQLanding.Answer3: Workers get paid directly into their checking accounts within 48 hours of each booking.
SectionFAQLanding.Answer4: We suggest setting your hourly rate about 50% higher than your normal hourly wage. After you receive some positive reviews, you can charge even more.{pageBreak}You can change your pricing instantly anytime. Our marketplace allows you to set your rate up to a maximum of $50 per hour.
SectionFAQLanding.Answer5: Our payment processor validates the identify of every worker at the time of registration. Workers must provide a picture of photo id and other supporting data.
SectionFAQLanding.Answer6: Restaurants incur a 12% fee on all booking costs.{pageBreak}Workers are charged a 5% platform fee. We waive this fee for workers that join before the Café Temps market launch in their area.

SectionWithCarousel.title: Our Workers Set Their Own Rates
SectionWithCarousel.sliderItem1Descripti: I have two years experience at Taco Bell. I've worked the drive thru and the register.
SectionWithCarousel.sliderItem2Descripti: I work at a coffee shop with bakery. I manage the front end, and keep customers happy.
